[]: Post by Sailor Star Dust &raquo; Thu Apr 14, 2011 5:26 pm The only real example I have is watching 1.0 in San Fran theaters with my stepsister: She found it interesting, but I guess wasn&#39;t interested enough to eventually check out 2.0. She&#39;s not as into anime as my stepbrother is, who&#39;s familiar with the series &#40;dunno about NME&#41; and feels &quot;it&#39;s a really good series&quot;. I think once I was watching a part of EoE with my stepmom or dad in the other room, and they were wondering why a feminine voice was screaming so much. Regarding the OP, I was personally on the flip side: When hearing about NGE in high school a friend was commenting how much ass Asuka kicks in EoE &#40;and another friend would sometimes play the MP3 of Misato&#39;s theme every so often&#41;...I was curious about Eva due to hearing it was psychological, but avoided it due to the mecha fights and thinking Anno was some egoistical asshole &#40;My opinion softened--greatly--upon learning he suffered from Depression with production of the show http://wiki.evageeks.org/User:Sailor_Star_Dust &#41;. Then in College, maybe a few months before I buckled down and watched the series, I asked a friend if the series was any good...They said it was, but told me the following: &quot;In EoE, Shinji says &quot;I&#39;m so fucked up....&quot; It seems that he FINALLY gets it!&quot;

